---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import Blade_Runner_2049_Limo_and_Spinner_02 from '../images/Blade-Runner-2049-Limo-and-Spinner-02-biloop.gif'
import Blade_Runner_2049_Header from '../images/Blade-Runner-2049-Header.gif'
import Blade_Runner_Concept_Header from '../images/Blade-Runner-Concept-Header.gif'
import door from '../images/maxresdefault.jpg'

const headerSrc = Blade_Runner_2049_Header.src
---

<section class="bg-primary">
    <Image
        id="image-1"
        class="w-full h-96 object-cover absolute border-b-2 inset-0 transition-opacity duration-1000 opacity-100"
        src={Blade_Runner_2049_Header}
        alt="Blade Runner 2049 Header"
        loading="lazy"
    />
    <Image
        id="image-2"
        class="w-full h-96 object-cover border-b-2 inset-0 transition-opacity duration-1000 opacity-0"
        src={Blade_Runner_Concept_Header}
        alt="Blade Runner Concept Header"
        loading="lazy"
    />

    <script is:inline>
        setTimeout(() => {
            const img1 = document.getElementById('image-1')
            const img2 = document.getElementById('image-2')
            img1.classList.remove('opacity-100')
            img1.classList.add('opacity-0')
            img2.classList.remove('opacity-0')
            img2.classList.add('opacity-100')
        }, 3630)
    </script>
    <div class="px-8 2xl:max-w-7xl mx-auto mb-64">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-y-24 gap-x-6">
            <div class="col-span-4 col-start-1"></div>
            <div
                class="col-span-1 pt-6 font-normal text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-7xl tracking-wider galach-font"
            >
                LEMUEL
            </div>
            <div
                class="col-start-2 col-span-3 pt-6 text-right md:text-sm text-xs font-light"
            >
                <script type="module" is:inline>
                    function getTimeInZone(timeZone) {
                        return new Date().toLocaleTimeString('en-GB', {
                            hour: '2-digit',
                            minute: '2-digit',
                            second: '2-digit',
                            hour12: false,
                            timeZone
                        })
                    }
                    function updateClocks() {
                        document.getElementById('nyc-clock').textContent =
                            getTimeInZone('America/New_York')
                        document.getElementById('lnd-clock').textContent =
                            getTimeInZone('Europe/London') // Handles BST/GMT
                        document.getElementById('hkg-clock').textContent =
                            getTimeInZone('Asia/Hong_Kong')
                    }
                    setInterval(updateClocks, 1000)
                    window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', updateClocks)
                </script>
                <div class="flex flex-row justify-end gap-4">
                    <div class="flex flex-col">
                        <div>NYC 紐約</div><span id="nyc-clock">--:--:--</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex flex-col">
                        <div>LND 倫敦</div><span id="lnd-clock">--:--:--</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex flex-col">
                        <div>HKG 香港</div><span id="hkg-clock">--:--:--</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="flex flex-col text-sm font-light divide-y-1 divide-dotted w-full"
            >
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-0 mb-6 pb-6">
                    <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/LemuelKL">
                        GitHub
                    </a>
                    <a
                        target="_blank"
                        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lemuelkl/"
                    >
                        LinkedIn
                    </a>
                    <a target="_blank" href="mailto:lemuellee.kl@gmail.com">
                        Email
                    </a>
                    <a target="_blank" href="https://blog.lemuellee.com">
                        Blog
                    </a>
                    <a target="_blank" href="/cv"> CV </a>
                </div>
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-0 mb-6 pb-6">
                    <div>Londoner</div>
                    <div>Hongkonger</div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-0">
                    <div>Cantonese</div>
                    <div>English</div>
                    <div>Mandarin</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <Image
                class="col-span-3 ml-auto"
                src={Blade_Runner_2049_Limo_and_Spinner_02}
                alt="Blade Runner 2049"
                loading="lazy"
            />
        </div>
        <div class="mt-64 text-xs grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <Image
                class="col-span-1"
                src={door}
                alt="Blade Runner 2049 Header"
                loading="lazy"
            />
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
                <div>
                    Lemuel was born and raised in Hong Kong, where the blend of
                    East and West shaped both his values and curiosities. He is
                    guided by a deep belief in individual liberty, free markets,
                    and the rule of law. He sees computing not just as a
                    profession, but as humanity's most powerful tool for
                    progress.
                </div>
                <div>
                    He wrote his first programs at age 12, driven by curiosity
                    more than instruction. That curiosity evolved into a formal
                    study of Computer Science at the University of Hong Kong,
                    where he also taught programming and explored everything
                    from operating systems to machine learning.
                </div>
                <div>
                    A semester abroad in the UK during the tail end of COVID-19
                    expanded his worldview — both culturally and intellectually
                    — introducing him to functional programming and language
                    design. He stayed on that summer for a pivotal internship as
                    a Quantitative Developer at Low Carbon Contracts Company,
                    where he gained insight into the intersection of markets,
                    policy, and climate.
                </div>
                <div>
                    Now pursuing a Master's at Imperial College London, Lemuel
                    is focused on applying data science to real-world energy
                    challenges. His current work involves building tools to
                    optimize energy use in data centers — bridging software and
                    sustainability, with the same spirit of independence that's
                    guided him since the beginning.
                </div>
                <div>
                    Outside of work, Lemuel finds inspiration in the quiet halls
                    of museums and the sweeping movements of classical music.
                    He's drawn to science fiction not just for its imagination,
                    but for what it says about our present. From military
                    technology to urban planning, fashion to political history,
                    his interests reflect a deep fascination with systems — how
                    things work, how they're designed, and how they could be
                    better. Whether he's studying the architecture of a city or
                    the structure of a musical composition, Lemuel sees patterns
                    everywhere — and in them, the potential for change, beauty,
                    and progress.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
